body.p: Dextormethorphan (DEX) liver model. DEX can be taken up by the liver and be converted to DOR via CYP2D6. This reaction can be inhibitited by substances such as quinidine.Within the liver part of the DEX can be metabolized via CYP3A4 mediated first-pass metabolism (the metabolic product of the reaction MEM is not part of the model), resulting in a reduced bioavailability of DEX.
